post_text:
Join us on #GIVINGTUESDAY to support The New School of San Francisco.

The New School of San Francisco is a first of its kind public school working to bring inquiry-based teaching to all children -- regardless of their background. Now in our 4th year, we serve 240 children from all corners of San Francisco. And as a laboratory school with a partnership with the Exploratorium's Institute for Inquiry, we are sharing our tools broadly to impact children and educators around the world.

We believe that education is our most powerful tool to change the world. Through inquiry and social justice, children develop the problem solving skills to be the change-makers of tomorrow.

https://www.paypal.com/fundraiser/108133408063901813/charity/116572

"As educators, we know what to do when a child is in pain. When they‚Äôre lost or afraid, we don‚Äôt wait to learn more about the situation. We don‚Äôt blame their parents for their choices. Ensuring that children feel safe and loved is our primary job as educators, and we cannot rest until we see that all children, whether in our own classrooms or not, are being spared from the pain of this inhumane policy."
